# Improved Application Workflow & UI Prompts

## 1. Upload Section with Validation

### 1.1 Month & Year Validation
- Automatically detect and validate file names against selected month/year from filter section
- Display clear error messages when file contains mismatched period data
- Provide option to auto-rename or skip mismatched files

### 1.2 Definition Fields Validation
- **Pre-upload Validation**: Compare file columns against predefined definition fields before allowing upload
- **Missing Fields Report**: Generate comprehensive list of missing required fields with column names and file references
- **Downloadable Error Log**: Provide CSV/Excel format error log with detailed explanation of validation failures
- **Sample Files**: Include downloadable template files with correct structure and required columns for each data type (Rural Market, Urban Market, House Rent, PDS, Electricity, etc.)

### 1.3 Upload Flow
- **Progressive Disclosure**: Upload section hides during processing, shows progress modal with detailed status
- **Failure Recovery**: On upload failure, show upload section again with error summary and option to retry with corrections
- **Success Transition**: After successful upload, display validation summary and auto-initiate compilation progress

### 1.4 Master Data Integration
- **Database-driven Validation**: All validation rules should reference master data tables (markets, items, COICOP codes) from database
- **Historical Index Data**: Fetch previous month/year indices from database for imputation and trend analysis
- **Reference Data Management**: Maintain central repository for weights, definitions, and classification codes

## 2. Compilation & Summary

### 2.1 Compilation Process
- **Real-time Progress**: Show method-wise compilation status with individual progress bars for each script (House Rent, Electricity, PDS, Fuel, Telecom, Postal/OTT, Railfare, Market Items, All India)
- **Status Indicators**: Color-coded status (Pending, Running, Completed, Failed) with estimated completion time
- **Error Handling**: If any method fails, show detailed error with option to retry only failed methods

### 2.2 Compilation Summary
- **Success View**: Display comprehensive summary with:
  - Rural indices breakdown (House Rent, PDS, Electricity, Fuel)
  - Urban indices breakdown (House Rent, Market Items, Telecom, Postal/OTT)
  - All India indices (CPI Rural, CPI Urban, CPI Combined)
  - Trend indicators (comparison with previous period)
  - Active "Import to Database" button prominently displayed
- **Failure View**: Show error summary with:
  - Failed methods list with error messages
  - Recommended actions
  - Option to retry or contact support

## 3. Filter Section & Date Logic

### 3.1 Compilation Types
- **Provisional (M-1)**:
  - Available only before 12th of current month
  - Shows countdown to compilation deadline
  - Auto-disables after cutoff date
- **Final (M-2)**:
  - Requires approval workflow for compilation
  - Shows approval status and history
  - Compilation allowed only after provisional data is frozen

### 3.2 Date-based Restrictions
- **Reference Date**: 12th of each month as compilation cutoff
- **Provisional Window**: 1st to 11th of current month
- **Final Window**: After provisional freeze, requires approver permission
- **Override Mechanism**: Admin/Approver can override freeze with justification note

### 3.3 Index Release Management
- **Release Workflow**: Approver can mark index as "Finalized" for public viewing
- **Access Control**: Before release, only Compiler/Approver can view; after release, all users can view
- **Version Control**: Maintain history of released indices with timestamps and user details

## 4. Outputs & Data Visualization

### 4.1 Weights Display
- **Rural/Urban Bifurcation**: Separate tabs/sections for Rural and Urban indices
- **Category-wise Breakdown**:
  - House Rent (HR) indices with sub-components
  - PDS items with individual item-level indices
  - Other categories (Fuel, Electricity, Telecom, etc.) with detailed breakdown
- **Interactive Charts**: Line charts showing index trends over time, bar charts comparing rural vs urban

### 4.2 COICOP Data Visualization
- **Hierarchical Display**: Expandable tree view showing COICOP classification at division, group, class, and item levels
- **Rural/Urban Toggle**: Switch between rural and urban weights and indices
- **Detailed Tables**: Show individual COICOP items with:
  - COICOP code and description
  - Rural weight
  - Urban weight
  - Combined weight
  - Current index values
  - Month-over-month changes
- **Data Export**: Option to export COICOP data in Excel/CSV format

### 4.3 Database Integration
- **Compiled Indices Section**: Pull real-time data from database tables showing:
  - Rural indices (house_rent, pds, electricity, fuel)
  - Urban indices (house_rent, market_items, telecom, postal_ott)
  - All India indices (cpi_rural, cpi_urban, cpi_combined)
- **Input Prices Section**: Display raw price data used for compilation with:
  - Market-wise price listings
  - Item-wise price trends
  - Comparison with previous periods
- **Search & Filter**: Allow users to filter by date range, sector, item category

### 4.4 Annexure Layout
- **Professional Format**: Create standardized annexure layout with:
  - Header: Title, month, year, compilation type
  - Main Table: COICOP-wise breakdown with weights and indices
  - Rural/Urban columns side by side for comparison
  - Footer: Source attribution and generation timestamp
- **Export Options**: Download as PDF, Excel, or CSV
- **Print-friendly**: Optimized for printing with proper pagination

## 5. Role-Based Access Control

### 5.1 User Roles
- **Compiler**: Can upload data, run compilation, view provisional results, cannot finalize
- **Approver**: Can review compilation, approve final release, override restrictions
- **Admin**: Full access including user management, configuration, and emergency overrides
- **Viewer**: Can only view finalized indices and reports

### 5.2 Access Rules
- **Pre-finalization**: Only Compiler and Approver can access compilation interface and provisional data
- **Post-finalization**: All authenticated users can view released indices
- **Emergency Override**: Admin can unlock frozen periods with audit trail

## 6. UI/UX Improvements

### 6.1 Navigation & Layout
- **Step-by-step Wizard**: Clear progress indicator showing current stage (Upload → Validate → Compile → Import → View)
- **Collapsible Sections**: Allow users to expand/collapse sections for focused work
- **Sticky Filters**: Keep filter section visible while scrolling for quick reference

### 6.2 Feedback & Notifications
- **Toast Notifications**: Non-intrusive success/error messages
- **Progress Indicators**: Animated progress bars with estimated time remaining
- **Status Badges**: Clear visual indicators for pending, in-progress, completed, failed states

### 6.3 Data Visualization
- **Interactive Charts**: Hover to see exact values, click to drill down
- **Comparison Views**: Side-by-side comparison of rural vs urban indices
- **Trend Analysis**: Show month-over-month and year-over-year changes

### 6.4 Export & Reporting
- **Multiple Formats**: Download reports as PDF, Excel, CSV
- **Custom Reports**: Allow users to select specific sections for export
- **Scheduled Reports**: Option to schedule automatic report generation

## 7. Workflow Optimization

### 7.1 Parallel Processing
- Allow multiple compilation scripts to run simultaneously
- Show individual progress for each method
- Failed methods don't block successful ones

### 7.2 Data Caching
- Cache master data (COICOP, weights, markets) for faster validation
- Pre-load previous period indices for trend calculation

### 7.3 Audit Trail
- Log all actions with timestamps and user details
- Maintain version history for all compiled indices
- Track approval/release workflow with comments

## 8. Error Handling & Recovery

### 8.1 Validation Failures
- Provide actionable error messages with specific file and column names
- Allow download of validation report
- Suggest corrections based on missing fields

### 8.2 Compilation Failures
- Show which specific script failed
- Provide error logs for debugging
- Allow retry of only failed methods
- Option to contact support with error details

### 8.3 Data Integrity
- Automatic backup before database import
- Rollback capability on import failure
- Validation checks before final database commit
